==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Castor
<hw>Cas"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>castor</ets>
the beaver, Gr. <?/; of uncertain origin.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of rodents, including the beaver. See
<er>Beaver</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Castoreum. See <er>Castoreum</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A hat, esp. one made of beaver fur; a
beaver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have always been known for the jaunty manner in which I wear my
<qex>castor</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A heavy quality of broadcloth for
overcoats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castor</ent>⟦br⟧

